  "aboutBody": [
    "Set on a working wharf in Bodega Bay, The Tides Wharf & Restaurant pairs fresh local seafood with sweeping views of the harbor, where guests watch fishing boats come and go and sea lions, otters, and shorebirds work the water. The original Tides Wharf is part of local lore as a filming location for Alfred Hitchcock’s The Birds.",
    "Open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner every day of the year, the restaurant is a classic Sonoma Coast destination — known for its to-go clam chowder, whole Dungeness crab, and cioppino, plus an espresso bar and an on-site fish market."
